"Beniston M., Casals P., Sarazin M.","Perturbations to astronomical observations at the European Southern Observatory's very large telescope site in Paranal, Chile: Analyses of climatological causes",2002,"Theoretical and Applied Climatology","73","3-4",,"133","150",,,10.1007/s00704-002-0700-x,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0036956459&partnerID=40&md5=dccf1d97534cf0dfb4dec9f691b9a5c0","Department of Geosciences, University of Fribourg, Switzerland; European Southern Observatory, Garching, Germany","Beniston, M., Department of Geosciences, University of Fribourg, Switzerland; Casals, P., Department of Geosciences, University of Fribourg, Switzerland; Sarazin, M., European Southern Observatory, Garching, Germany","A study has been conducted to assess the reasons for a significant decrease in the astronomic observing period since the Very Large Telescope of ESO (the European Southern Observatory) went into operation in 1998. Following a multi-year monitoring of meteorological parameters at the site of the ESO telescope in Paranal (northern Chile), the optimal climatic conditions observed there prior to the construction of the Very Large Telescope have not been as frequently recorded since. In order to determine whether this region is being subjected to long-term changes in climate consecutive to 20th century global warming, or whether the ENSO (El Niño/Southern Oscillation) event in the final years of the 1990s are responsible for this situation, climatological data from in situ measurements, upper-air soundings, analogical reconstructions of meteorological data to extend the records further back into the past, and large-scale re-analysis data have been used. The results point towards a dominant role of ENSO in the current problems that astronomers face with reduced observation time.",,"astronomy; climate change; climate forcing; El Nino-Southern Oscillation; observatory; perturbation; Chile",,,,,,"Aceituno, P., Fuenzalida, H., Rosenbluth, B., Climate along the extratropical west coast of South America (1993) Part II: Climate Controls. Earth System Responses to Global Change: Contrasts Between North and South America, pp. 61-72. , Mooney H, Fuentes E, Kronberg B (eds) Dortrecht, The Netherlands: Kluwer Academic Publishers; Barros, V., Castaneda, M.E., Doyle, M., Recent precipitation trends in South America to the East of the Andes: An indication of climatic variability (1999) Southern Hemisphere Paleo and Neoclimates: Concepts and Problems, , Volheimer W, Smolka P (eds) Berlin, Heidelberg: Springer; Cantaneda, M.E., Barros, V., Las tendencias de precipitación en el Cono Sur de América al este de los Andes (1993) Meteorológica, p. 19; Compagnucci, R.H., Influencia del ENSO en el desarrollo socio económico de Cuyo (1991) Anales CONGREMET VI, pp. 95-96. , 23-27 March 1991, Buenos Aires, Argentina. Centro Argentino de Meteorólogos, Argentina; Compagnucci, R.H., Impact of ENSO events on the hydrological system of the Cordillera the los Andes during the last 450 years (2000) Southern Hemisphere Paleo and Neoclimates: Concepts, Methods and Problems, , Volheimer W. Smolka P (eds) Berlin, Heidelberg: Springer; Compagnucci, R.H., Vargas, W.M., Interannual variability of the Cuyo River's streamflow in the Argentinian Andean mountains and ENSO events (1998) Int J Climatol, 18, pp. 1593-1609; Diaz, H.F., Graham, N.E., Recent changes in tropical freezing heights and the role of sea-surface temperature (1996) Nature, 383, pp. 152-155; Eltahir, E.A.B., Wang, G., El Niño and climate variability (1999) Geophys Res Lett, 26 (4), p. 489; Erasmus, D.A., The effects of El Niño-Southern Oscillation on the seasonal, inter-annual and spatial variability of water vapour and cirrus cloud cover over Northern Chile (1998) A Satellite-Derived Climatology of Water Vapour and Cirrus Cloud Cover in the Area of Chajnantor, Northern Chile, , http://www.eso.org/genfac/pubs/astclim/espas/radioseeing/erasmus/ proposal1-htm, This document can be f